{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2e8a834b-6b67-444e-8f98-7563aa4511f1","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so I'll give you general guidance on switching to **NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC)**.\n\n---\n\n### Key changes to your GitHub Actions workflow\n\n**1. Add `id-token: write` permission** so the runner can request an OIDC token:\n\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # Required for OIDC\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**2. Replace `dotnet nuget push --api-key` with the OIDC-based step.** Use the official `dotnet` CLI trusted publishing flow:\n\n```yaml\n- name: Push to NuGet (trusted publishing)\n  run: dotnet nuget push \"**/*.nupkg\" --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n  # No --api-key needed; authentication is handled via OIDC token\n```\n\n**3. Remove `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY`** from the workflow — it's no longer needed.\n\n---\n\n### On the NuGet.org side\n\n1. Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → your package → Trusted Publishers**.\n2. Add a **GitHub Actions** trusted publisher entry with:\n   - **Repository owner** (e.g., `my-org`)\n   - **Repository name** (e.g., `my-repo`)\n   - **Workflow filename** (e.g., `publish.yml`)\n   - Optionally restrict to a specific **branch/tag** or **environment**.\n\n---\n\n### Minimal before/after\n\n```yaml\n# BEFORE\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n\n# AFTER (with id-token: write in permissions)\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nThe OIDC token is automatically passed by the `dotnet` CLI when no API key is provided and trusted publishing is configured on nuget.org. No secrets to rotate or leak.\n\nWant me to create or update a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dfcc7d88-e432-4b35-a40f-1bc46a1ff0f4","outputTokens":520},"id":"9b6945a2-5385-48fc-8f48-15bc0597c856","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:45:14.773Z","parentId":"d55ae896-d1b2-4574-ab51-dd82d4c8fc35"}
